name: Cardboard
description: Corrugated and non-corrugated cardboard can be recycled together. They can be broken down and made into new boxes and packaging materials.

name: Paper
description: Includes office paper, printer paper, and copy paper. It can be recycled into new paper products.

name: Envelopes
description: They can be recycled with paper, as long as they do not have any plastic windows.

name: Colored Paper
description: Can be recycled with other paper, but the color may not be retained in the recycling process.

name: Magazine
description: Can be recycled with paper, but glossy pages may need to be separated.

name: Newspaper
description: Can be recycled with other paper.

name: Paper Bag
description: Can be recycled with other paper, but handle may need to be removed.

name: Paper Cup
description: Some paper cups are lined with plastic, which means they can't be recycled. Check with your local recycling program to see if they accept them.

name: Book
description: Books can be recycled, but they can also be donated to libraries or schools.

name: Shredded Paper
description: Can be recycled with other paper, but it should be placed in a clear plastic bag before being placed in the recycling bin.

name: Wrapping Paper
description: Wrapping paper can be recycled, but it should be free of any foil, glitter or plastic additions.

name: Paper Carton
description: Cartons that have held items such as juice, broth or soy milk can be recycled.

name: Juice Box
description: Juice boxes can be recycled, but it should be rinsed clean, and the straw removed.

name: Aseptic Paper
description: Aseptic containers, such as milk or juice cartons can be recycled.

name: Bottle
description: Made of plastic or glass, bottles can be recycled.

name: Takeout Container
description: Some takeout containers can be recycled, but it depends on the material. Check with your local recycling program to see if they accept them.

name: Milk Jug
description: Can be recycled, but should be rinsed clean.

name: Plastic Cup
description: Some plastic cups can be recycled, but it depends on the material. Check with your local recycling program to see if they accept them.

name: Plastic Bucket
description: Can be recycled, but should be clean and free of any food residue.

name: Plastic Furniture
description: Can be recycled, but it depends on the type and location. Check with your local recycling program to see if they accept them.

name: Laundry Basket
description: Can be recycled, but it depends on the type and location. Check with your local recycling program to see if they accept them.

name: Aluminum Can
description: Can be recycled and made into new products.

name: Aluminum Foil
description: Can be recycled, but should be clean and free of any food residue.

name: Tin Can
description: Can be recycled and made into new products.

name: Scrap Metal
description: Can be recycled and made into new products.

name: Glass Bottle
description: Can be recycled and made into new products.

name: Glass Jars
description: Can be recycled and made into new products.

name: Trash
description: Cannot be recycled
